{"_id": "543a2f178169243c", "name": "Acrobatics", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "STR+DEX", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Acrobatics covers acts of balance, gymnastics, juggling, and tumbling. With a successful roll a character can move at full speed across an unstable or narrow surface. When mitigating damage from an unexpected fall a successful roll halves damage sustained. If the character does not suffer a Serious or Major Wound from the fall, they land safely and are not prone. Acrobatics can substitute for Evade, with the benefit that the character automatically regains their footing rather than being rendered prone.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "c572bce9f6a129de", "name": "Acting", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "CHA*2", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Acting governs the ability to impersonate and convey a completely different character, whether in a staged performance or a social situation. The actor portrays a personality and mannerisms different to their own in a convincing manner. Coupled with Disguise and Deceit, this is a powerful way of becoming someone else entirely.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "0b1a54999d07d1c7", "name": "Art", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "POW+CHA", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "There are many specific art forms: Painting, Poetry, Literature, Sculpture, and more. A character chooses an Art specialisation when taking this skill. Subsequent Art forms are advanced separately. A roll is made whenever a character must impress or convince through their artistic medium.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "53d8cd452733b27b", "name": "Astrogation", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "INT*2", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Astrogation is equivalent to Navigation but enables starship pilots to plot a course at stellar and interstellar distances. It is used in science fiction and space opera settings.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "f31236a7c34f4499", "name": "Bureaucracy", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "INT*2", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Understanding administrative procedures, records, and unspoken conventions is covered by Bureaucracy. It is used to interact with officials or discover pertinent civic information. Whenever red tape or administrative landscapes need to be navigated, a Bureaucracy roll is necessary.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "7f269ddfa37416c9", "name": "Commerce", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "INT+CHA", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Commerce is used to evaluate the worth of goods and commodities and to trade them for the best possible price. It also covers the intricacies of business transactions, securing a profit, and finding ways to dispose of stolen or illicit goods. Commerce can be opposed by an opponent's Commerce skill or Willpower, reflecting the opposing side's attempts to further the deal in their favour.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "c6f271661118b569", "name": "Comms", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "INT*2", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Comms grants the ability to use communications equipment to detect, conceal, or block communications traffic. It also grants a chance of cracking encrypted messages, providing the user has access to a code-cracker.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "6cc356e61fd1c064", "name": "Computers", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "INT*2", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Computers reflects the ability to solve complex problems or extract complex information using computer systems \u2014 through programming code, detailed use of software, hacking, and diagnosing or repairing software and hardware problems. General use of computers does not usually require a roll.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "92a0891fabc7bee4", "name": "Courtesy", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "INT+CHA", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Courtesy covers understanding how to act appropriately in a social or formal situation: modes of address, rituals, and conventions of behaviour. It includes everything from who to bow to and when, from when to use a particular title to when it is appropriate to act informally.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "3dcf2989df8e8310", "name": "Craft", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "DEX+INT", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Each Craft is a specialised form \u2014 there are as many crafts as there are professions for them. Craft is used to create the subject item. How long it takes depends on the nature of the product. The skill reflects the crafter's technique, the quality of their resources, and their attention to detail. Each specialisation (e.g. Craft (Blacksmithing)) is advanced separately.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "93f46bda6e310f90", "name": "Culture", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "INT*2", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Culture is the more specific form of the Standard Skill of Customs, relating to societies foreign to the character's own. Each Culture skill must be given a particular nation or society to which it applies. It works mechanically in the same way as the Customs skill.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "0900b147a8107297", "name": "Demolitions", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "INT+POW", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Demolitions permits a character to safely handle and utilise explosive materials, whether setting them up or disarming them.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "5096a5e8e354b6a3", "name": "Disguise", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "INT+CHA", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Effecting a convincing disguise using appropriate materials (costumes, cosmetics, wigs, or hairpieces) is covered by Disguise. Creating the disguise requires time, attention to detail, and access to the right materials. If some or all of these elements are absent, the Difficulty Grade is increased. Disguise can be augmented with Acting to enhance the overall effect of a deception.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "5685aa0a2f334165", "name": "Electronics", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "DEX+INT", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Electronics allows the user to tinker with, bypass, or repair electronic devices. It has many applications, most often to temporarily patch up damaged equipment or replace broken circuits with spares.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "03bc1dafda19c78f", "name": "Engineering", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "INT*2", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "The design and building of large-scale structures \u2014 from houses to bridges, gates to siege engines \u2014 is in the remit of Engineering. Rolls are necessary when planning large-scale projects to ensure correct construction, and also when an engineer wants to assess a structure's integrity or locate weak spots.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "3dbd1a1547421583", "name": "Forgery", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "DEX+INT", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Forgery permits the creation or falsification of official documentation.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "a66f1b2eef8769d4", "name": "Gambling", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "INT+POW", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Gambling measures competence in games of chance where money is staked on the outcome. It is used to assess the odds of success or failure, or spot when someone is cheating. Gambling can be used in an opposed or unopposed manner depending on the situation.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "559a7028229d0bb9", "name": "Healing", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "INT+POW", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Healing is the in-depth knowledge of medical procedures based on cultural practices. It is used to treat serious injuries (typically those where Hit Points are at zero or less). It includes setting bones, suturing wounds, and applying poultices or drugs as appropriate to the setting. Applying Healing requires appropriate resources such as needles, thread, herbs, or a medical kit.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "66c0b91a51987fd6", "name": "Language", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "INT+CHA", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Language covers speaking and comprehension of a language other than the character's own. It is treated as a static representation of overall fluency: 1-25% a few basic words; 26-50% simple sentences; 51-75% fluent for general conversation; 76+% able to converse eloquently. Language can act as a cap for certain other skills such as Bureaucracy where fluency is a limiting factor.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "cfcaeda6ee0d7fca", "name": "Linguistics", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "INT*2", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Linguistics is the academic study of languages, allowing the character to analyse unknown languages, decipher codes, and understand the structure and evolution of speech and writing systems.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "b2f0095bcac3ad76", "name": "Literacy", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "INT*2", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Speaking a language fluently does not mean one can read and write it. Literacy is specific to a particular language and must be learned separately. In some societies it is reserved for the nobility or clergy; in modern settings it is learned by default and does not require a separate skill.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "09935cea4ff64eae", "name": "Lockpicking", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "DEX*2", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Lockpicking is the ability to open a mechanical locking system without the aid of a key. It includes the techniques of levering open bolted or barred doors and windows without causing damage. Lockpicking may also be used to lock something when no key is available.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "da7dc8ea6336d43e", "name": "Lore", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "INT*2", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Lore covers a specific body of knowledge chosen when the skill is first learned: Alchemy, Astrology, Geography, Heraldry, History, Monsters, Religion, Strategy and Tactics, and many more. Skill in a Lore means the character understands its fundamentals, how it can be applied to immediate challenges, and can use it to recall useful information. Each specialisation is advanced separately.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "f3c02c934636f13f", "name": "Magic", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "POW+CHA", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "The Magic skill is used for casting the spells described in the Powers chapter. A successful roll is needed for a spell to work, although the spell may still be resisted by an opposing skill such as Willpower.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "6e103e6f760280ce", "name": "Mechanisms", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "DEX+INT", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Mechanisms represents the knowledge and skill to assemble and disassemble mechanical devices such as traps. It generally involves the creation of delicate contraptions with small working parts, as opposed to Engineering which deals with massive constructions. It is a distinct discipline from Lockpicking and cannot be interchanged with that skill.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "cabfb31a3b094538", "name": "Musicianship", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "DEX+CHA", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Musicianship covers the playing of musical instruments. Each iteration applies to a group of similar instruments \u2014 a musician who can play a reed pipe can also play a flute or panpipes, but not a harp. Musicianship is advanced separately for each instrument family.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "331c08e1d1b22880", "name": "Navigation", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "INT+POW", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Navigation covers the ability to accurately direct travel using landmarks, the stars, or other environmental cues. Each Navigation skill covers a specific region or environment (Open Seas, Underground, and so on). A roll should be made during unusual journeys or when in completely unfamiliar territory.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "0b46b238f39fed55", "name": "Oratory", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "POW+CHA", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Oratory is the art of delivering a speech to a large group of people with the aim of conveying or swaying a point of view. It is used by politicians to drive home a policy and by commanders to inspire troops. Wherever mass persuasion is needed, Oratory rather than Influence is used.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "7269a64ef4abf1a2", "name": "Pilot", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "DEX+INT", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "The Pilot skill permits the control of a specified class of flying vehicles (such as gliders, prop-driven planes, jet engines, and so on). Each class of vehicle may be a separate specialisation.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "4450ee91bdcbbcc7", "name": "Politics", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "INT+CHA", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Characters with the Politics skill understand how to navigate and negotiate the corridors of government at local and national levels.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "c0cf909a8e996be4", "name": "Research", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "INT+POW", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Research uses various resources \u2014 such as a library, newspaper archive, or computer network \u2014 to discover desired pieces of information.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "da0138b9fc96c822", "name": "Science", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "INT*2", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "There are dozens of scientific disciplines and Science is always associated with one: Science (Biology), Science (Chemistry), and so on. Science replaces the Lore skill in modern and futuristic settings. Each specialisation is advanced separately.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "1ca5972c6fbc5142", "name": "Seamanship", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "INT+CON", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Seamanship is used in the same way as Boating but applied to large waterborne vessels powered by sail or banks of oars. It also covers the maintenance and upkeep of a ship: assessing when repairs are needed, where it is safe to anchor, and the dangers of violent weather.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "9e2166c346873721", "name": "Seduction", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "INT+CHA", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Seduction is the romantic or sexual persuasion of another person, very different to Influence. It uses explicit signals \u2014 verbal and non-verbal \u2014 to elicit a sexually positive response. Successful Seduction may take hours, days, or weeks depending on the morals of the target, who can attempt to resist with Willpower.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "762ab82bd1947099", "name": "Sensors", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "INT+POW", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Sensors allows the accurate use and analysis of sensor devices, from chemical sniffers up to military long-range scanners.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "7fbe9a15dea28cee", "name": "Sleight", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "DEX+CHA", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Sleight covers attempts to palm or conceal small objects (legerdemain and prestidigitation) and includes attempts to pick pockets, cut purses, or cause a visual distraction. It is an essential skill for thieves and stage magicians alike.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "8dcc6f94845f1a13", "name": "Streetwise", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "POW+CHA", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Streetwise represents knowledge of places and social contacts within a settlement. It covers everything from identifying potentially dangerous neighbourhoods to finding local services \u2014 legal or illegal. How long a Streetwise attempt takes depends on what is being sought.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "5af4a807f0c084b5", "name": "Survival", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "CON+POW", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Survival covers surviving in a rural or wilderness environment where the benefits of civilisation are absent: foraging, building a fire, finding shelter or a safe place to sleep. When properly equipped, rolls are usually unnecessary. Only when separated from equipment or when conditions turn bad does it become essential. A roll is usually made once per day in such conditions.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "741d9f1dcba79e33", "name": "Teach", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "INT+CHA", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Teach allows the user to pass on their knowledge and techniques in an easy to understand and constructive manner. Without this skill, even the most capable of masters will have difficulty instructing others effectively.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
{"_id": "4bd1f7b9ba9e00b8", "name": "Track", "type": "skill", "img": "icons/svg/skill.svg", "system": {"category": "professional", "baseFormula": "INT+CON", "baseValue": 0, "bonusPoints": 0, "total": 0, "description": "Track is used for tracking any form of game or quarry. It uses both obvious and subtle signs of passing to remain on the quarry's trail \u2014 footprints, bruised leaves, scattered pollen, displaced rocks, and other tell-tale signs invisible to the unskilled. Track rolls are needed periodically as conditions change. Conceal rolls can be used to oppose a Track roll.", "fumbledLastSession": false}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "flags": {}}
